08/10/2006
KORCA, Albania -- The new regional court of appeals building in Korca opened on Friday (October 6th) with a ceremony attended by European Commission Ambassador Helmuth Lohan, Albanian President Alfred Moisiu, Justice Minister Aldo Bumci and other top judicial officials. The project was financed under the EU CARDS programme. Lohan said the Union would continue to support the restructuring and modernisation of Albania's judicial sector and the upgrading of domestic legislation in line with EU standards. (Albanian News - 07/10/06; Albanian President website - 06/10/06)
